hwdot1sMstiMasterBridgeID.description: The Bridge Idnetifier of the current Master Bridge. Effective in CIST.

hwdot1sMstiMasterPortCost.description: The CIST path cost from the transmitting Bridge to the Master Bridge. Effective in CIST.

hwdot1sMstiStpPortPointToPoint.description: Whether the port connects the point to point link. Effective in CIST.

hwdot1sMstiStpTXTCNBPDU.description: The number of transimitted TCN BPDU. Effective in CIST.

hwdot1sMstiStpRXRSTPBPDU.description: The number of received RST BPDU. Effective in CIST.

hwdot1sMstiStpTXRSTPBPDU.name: hwdot1sMstiStpTXRSTPBPDU
hwdot1sMstiStpTXRSTPBPDU.description: The number of transimitted RST BPDU. Effective in CIST.

hwdot1sMstiStpRXMSTPBPDU.description: The number of received MST BPDU. Effective in CIST.

hwdot1sMstiPortLoopGuard.description: Whether the loop protection is enabled. Effective in CIST.

hwdot1sMstiStpPortSendingBPDUType.name: hwdot1sMstiStpPortSendingBPDUType
hwdot1sMstiStpPortSendingBPDUType.description: Type of BPDU which the port is sending.

hwdot1sMstiStpOperPortPointToPoint.name: hwdot1sMstiStpOperPortPointToPoint
hwdot1sMstiStpOperPortPointToPoint.description: This object indicates whether the port has connected to a point-to-point link or not. The value of the node is an operative value. The administrative value can be read from the node hwdot1sMstiStpPortPointToPoint. If the value of hwdot1sMstiStpPortPointToPoint is auto, the value of this node should be calculated by the network topology of this port. If the value of hwdot1sMstiStpPortPointToPoint is forceFalse, the value of this node is false. If the value of hwdot1sMstiStpPortPointToPoint is forceTrue, the value of this node is true.

hwdot1sMstiStpPortAdminBPDUFmt.name: hwdot1sMstiStpPortAdminBPDUFmt
hwdot1sMstiStpPortAdminBPDUFmt.description: The value of the node is an administrative value. Value legacy means that the MST BPDU format is forced to legacy. Value dot1s means that the MST BPDU format is forced to IEEE 802.1s. Value auto means that the format of MST BPDU sending on the port is determined by the MST BPDU that the port has received. Effective in CIST.

hwdot1sMstiStpPortOperBPDUFmt.name: hwdot1sMstiStpPortOperBPDUFmt
hwdot1sMstiStpPortOperBPDUFmt.description: The format of MST BPDU which the port is sending. Value legacy means that the format of MST BPDU sending on the port is legacy. Value dot1s means that the format of MST BPDU sending on the port is IEEE 802.1s. Effective in CIST.

hwdot1sMstiStpPortRoleRestriction.name: hwdot1sMstiStpPortRoleRestriction
hwdot1sMstiStpPortRoleRestriction.description: Whether the role-restriction is enabled. Effective in CIST. The role-restriction causes the port not to be selected as root port for the CIST or any MSTI.

hwdot1sMstiStpPortTcRestriction.name: hwdot1sMstiStpPortTcRestriction
hwdot1sMstiStpPortTcRestriction.description: Whether the tc-restriction is enabled. Effective in CIST. The tc-restriction causes the port not to propagate topology changes to other ports.

hwdot1sMstiStpPortDisputed.name: hwdot1sMstiStpPortDisputed
hwdot1sMstiStpPortDisputed.description: Whether the port is disputed for the CIST or MSTI.

hwdot1sStpPathCostStandard.name: hwdot1sStpPathCostStandard
hwdot1sStpPathCostStandard.description: Path cost standard of the bridge. Value dot1d-1998 is IEEE 802.1d standard in 1998, value dot1t is IEEE 802.1t standard, and value legacy is a private legacy standard.

hwPortMstiStateDiscarding.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when a port turns into discarding state form forwarding state.

hwBridgeLostRootPrimary.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when the bridge is no longer the root bridge of the instance. Another switch with higher priority has already been the root bridge of the instance.

hwPortMstiRootGuarded.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when a root-guard port receives a superior message on the relevant instance.

hwPortMstiBpduGuarded.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when an edged port of the BPDU-guard switch receives BPDU packets.
